# !! DO NOT ADD MORE ENTRIES HERE without per-entry preview-deploy verification.
#
# History:
# - 3d425f00 added 11 dir excludes at once → prod 500'd with ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND.
# - 6ccffc1b tried a 9-dir "safe subset" → same outage.
# - 2026-04-22 bisection (branch bisect/vercelignore-twin-research) confirmed
#   `twin-research/` alone causes FUNCTION_INVOCATION_FAILED. Unknown transitive
#   reference — grep finds no static imports, but nft's trace needs it present.
#   Never add `twin-research/` here.
# - Other candidates (scripts/, mobile/, database/, design-system/, tests/,
#   test-data/, coverage/, playwright-report/, tmp/, tasks/, .github/) not
#   yet individually verified. If re-introducing, push as its own branch
#   `bisect/vercelignore-<dir>`, use `vercel curl` or the Vercel MCP
#   `web_fetch_vercel_url` tool to probe the preview's /api/health — preview
#   URLs are SSO-gated so plain curl returns 401 regardless of health.
#
# If build time is the pain, the right approach is to extract more handlers
# to standalone Vercel functions (like api/webhook-pluggy.js) instead of
# tightening the ignore list.
